gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Suns 116, Bulls 115
gameRecap.excerpt: The Suns defeated the Bulls in overtime, 116-115. Grayson Allen recorded 26 points, including a career-high eight 3pt FGM for the Suns, while Kevin Durant added 25 points, eight rebounds, and nine assists in the victory. DeMar DeRozan and Zach LaVine each tallied 22 points for the Bulls in the losing effort. The Suns improve to 4-4 on the season, while the Bulls fall to 3-6.
